# Trivy ignore file — odoocker-goldberrygrove
#
# Format: one CVE ID per line. Optional `exp:YYYY-MM-DD` suffix sets an
# expiration after which Trivy re-flags the entry, forcing a periodic re-review.
#
# Scope ignores as tightly as possible. Each entry must be justified by a
# comment immediately above it explaining:
#   1. why the CVE doesn't apply (or is mitigated) in our deployment
#   2. the expected fix path (upstream patch, base image rev, removal of dep)
#
# Reference: https://aquasecurity.github.io/trivy/latest/docs/configuration/filtering/
